Hi Prof. Goodwin
  I have found a small bug in ck2cti:
in Cantera/src/converters/ck2ct.cpp:422

  fprintf(f,  "\n# [CK Reaction (%s)]\n",i+1);  

should be

  fprintf(f,  "\n# [CK Reaction (%d)]\n",i+1);  

isn't it?
W/o correction I get a segmentation fault at this point. I am running
Cantera on a Linux box, FC4, pentium IV.

Massimiliano
